commit bff6cd9a05ab153af2135c49cfba5ba0f9e12d79
Author: Cyrene Ireland <cyrenei@proton.me>
Date:   Thu Apr 9 20:38:23 2026 -0600

    resolve 107 design-failure findings from security audit
    
    14 crates analyzed via /design-failure, 4 composition boundary audits.
    155 total findings (24 CRIT, 60 HIGH, 52 MED, 19 LOW), 107 resolved.
    
    crit fixes:
    - proxy body size limits (Limited wrapper, 10MB default)
    - proxy connection timeouts (30s upstream, 10s header read)
    - credential zeroization (HashMap<String, SecretString>)
    - session fixation prevention (agent_id binding check)
    - delegation chain scope_narrowing enforcement in policy eval
    - audit blake3 hash chain implementation
    - default signing secret removed (empty = rejected)
    - behavior detect_with_args wired into production path
    - cli sha256 verification moved in-process (sha2 crate)
    - metrics PII prevention (label allowlist + sanitization)
    - credential injection gated on session validation
    - nonmcp post denied when policies configured
    - body canonicalization eliminates parser differential
    - batch parsing rejects malformed jsonrpc items
    - introspection validates iss/aud/exp against config
    
    high fixes:
    - upstream url scheme validation at startup
    - security header stripping before forwarding
    - connection concurrency semaphore (1024 default)
    - path traversal prevention (percent-decode + dot-collapse)
    - policy watcher initial synchronous load
    - dot-path traversal for parameter constraints
    - storage-backed registry expiry check
    - cross-owner delegation prevention
    - atomic session creation cap (create_if_under_cap)
    - storage write-through error propagation
    - graceful shutdown with joinset drain
    - policy load failure blocks startup
    - per-client rate limiting (keyed by api key hash)
    - delegation chain populated from session snapshot
    - trust demotion aborts in-flight request
    - credential access control per session
    - token scope extraction (typed Claims.scope field)
    - audit stats after write (not before)
    - argument scanning all tiers (not just read/unknown)
    - escalate_to_deny defaults to true
    - encryption key versioning for rotation
    - redirect uri validation field
    
    med/low fixes:
    - method allowlist middleware (blocks TRACE/CONNECT)
    - case-insensitive tool matching
    - duplicate policy id detection in compile()
    - kid removed from error display
    - audience validation disabled warning
    - redaction depth limit (64)
    - batch size cap (100)
    - uuid validation in cli url construction
    - http:// warning for non-loopback
    - doctor command read-only (no policy reload)
    - json-rpc id validation (type + size)
    - file provider reload support (Arc<RwLock>)
    - unicode normalization resistance in arg scanning
    - close_sessions lock released before storage writes
    - opaque error messages in lifecycle api
    - policy file path removed from reload response
    - scrub_response_plain deprecated
    - session minimum time_limit (1s)
    - list_agents filters deactivated/expired
    - metrics render uses from_utf8 not lossy
    - delegation chain max depth (10)
    - empty scope_narrowing rejected
    - jwks cache guards against empty replacement
    - agent-scoped session listing
    - persistent audit file handle
    - authorization_decision validation
    - audit max file size config

